# Gaze Tracker — Full Rewrite with MediaPipe, Head Pose, Blink Analysis & Multi-Person Detection

The existing [gaze_tracker.py](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/gaze_tracker.py) is a simple 108-line script using the [gaze_tracking](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/gaze_tracker.py#15-100) library with basic left/right/center classification. It needs a complete rewrite to match the Feature 1.1 specification: MediaPipe Face Mesh for 468 landmarks, head pose estimation, EAR-based blink analysis, YOLOv8 multi-person detection, and a proper alert/flag system with JSON logging.

## Proposed Changes

### Gaze Tracker Core

#### [MODIFY] [gaze_tracker.py](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/gaze_tracker.py)

Complete rewrite from a bare function to a `GazeTracker` class (matching the project's class-based pattern from [EmotionTracker](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/emotion_detection.py#19-113), [FaceVerifier](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/face_verification.py#15-108), [PersonDetector](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/person_detection.py#14-87)).

**Key features:**

| Feature | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **Face Presence** | MediaPipe Face Mesh — check if mesh detected, compute face bounding box vs frame center |
| **Gaze Direction** | Iris landmarks (468–477) mapped to gaze vector; classify LEFT/RIGHT/UP/DOWN/CENTER |
| **Head Pose** | `cv2.solvePnP` with 6 canonical 3D face points → pitch/yaw/roll angles |
| **Blink Analysis** | EAR (Eye Aspect Ratio) per frame; track blinks/min, flag if outside 12–20 range |
| **Multi-Person** | YOLOv8 (`ultralytics`) on full frame; >1 person = instant alert |
| **Alert Thresholds** | 3s off-screen → `SOFT_FLAG`; 10s off-screen → `HARD_FLAG` + screenshot |
| **Output** | JSON flag log: `{timestamp, severity, type, details}` |

**Core methods:**
- [__init__()](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/emotion_detection.py#22-27) — initialize MediaPipe, YOLO, state trackers
- [analyze_frame(frame)](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/main.py#242-314) — single-frame analysis returning all detections (called by `/api/analyze-frame`)
- `_detect_face_presence(landmarks, frame_shape)` — face centered/in-frame check
- `_estimate_gaze(landmarks)` — iris-based gaze direction
- `_estimate_head_pose(landmarks, frame_shape)` — yaw/pitch/roll via solvePnP
- `_compute_ear(landmarks)` — Eye Aspect Ratio for blink detection
- `_detect_persons(frame)` — YOLOv8 person count
- [build_report()](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/emotion_detection.py#91-113) — aggregate flags, blink stats, gaze log into final report
- [run(duration)](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/emotion_detection.py#34-90) — standalone webcam loop (for testing, like other services)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The [analyze_frame(frame)](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/main.py#242-314) method is the key integration point — [main.py](file:///c:/Users/ACER/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/Intelligent_AI_Interview_Platform/ai-services/main.py) sends individual frames from the frontend via base64, so the tracker must work **per-frame** (stateful across calls), not as a standalone webcam loop.

